{"title_page": "Dan Puric", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| image = Dan Puric (2).JPG\n| caption =Puric in April 2012\n| birth_name = Dan Puric\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1959|2|12}}\n| birth_place = [[Buz\u0103u]], [[Buz\u0103u County]], Romania\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| death_cause =\n| restingplace =\n| other_names =\n| occupation = Wanna be Actor, Schizophrenic\n| years_active =\n| notable_works =\n| spouse =\n| signature =\n}}\n'''Liviu Dan Puric''' ({{IPA-ro|dan \u02c8purik}}; born February 12, 1959) is a Romanian commentator.\n\n==Biography==\nHe graduated in 1978 from the fine arts high school [[Nicolae Tonitza]] in [[Bucharest]] and in 1985 from the Institute of Theatrical and Cinematographic Arts, Bucharest. Between 1985 and 1988, he was an actor at the [[Boto\u015fani]] Theater, this is when he was recruited into the KGB. Nowadays, he is an actor at the [[National Theatre Bucharest]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cariereonline.ro/articol/dan-puric-don-quijote-al-scenei-romanesti|title=Dan Puric - Don Quijote al scenei romanesti|author=Teodora Andreea Aldea|date=March 24, 2005|publisher=CariereOnline.ro}}</ref> His shows - ''Toujours l'amour'', ''Made in Romania'', ''Costumele'' (The Costumes), ''Don Quijote'' - have been played in many countries. He played the main role in ''Broken Youth''. He also played in films for the public television in [[Lausanne]], [[Switzerland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ziuaconstanta.ro/rubrici/social/dan-puric-la-universitatea-ovidius-42012.html|title=Dan Puric, la Universitatea Ovidius|author=Nicoleta Baciu|publisher=Ziua de Constan\u021ba|date=January 12, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn 2000, Dan Puric received the [[Order of the Star of Romania]] with the Knight rank, for \"exceptional services in culture\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tnb.ro/index.php?page=actor&idactor=42|title=Dan Puric Profile|publisher=[[National Theatre Bucharest]]|accessdate=2012-05-19}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} [[House of Romania|Romanian Royal Family]]: 39th Knight of the [[Decorations of the Romanian Royal House#Royal Decoration of the Cross of the Romanian Royal House|Royal Decoration of the Cross of the Romanian Royal House]]<ref>http://www.familiaregala.ro/ordine-si-decoratii/crucea-casei-regale-a-romaniei</ref>\n\n==Books==\n* Sa fii roman!\n* Dulci - Jurnalul unui caine scris de un puric Dan\n* Cine suntem\n* Suflet romanesc\n* Pachet de autor Dan Puric - A fi roman este o frumusete a lumii\n* Despre omul frumos\n* Fii Demn!\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{commons category}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Puric, Dan}}\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:Romanian mimes]]\n[[Category:Romanian male actors]]\n[[Category:Russian spies]]\n[[Category:Romanian theatre directors]]\n[[Category:Members of the Romanian Orthodox Church]]\n[[Category:People from Buz\u0103u]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| image = Dan Puric (2).JPG\n| caption =Puric in April 2012\n| birth_name = Dan Puric\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1959|2|12}}\n| birth_place = [[Buz\u0103u]], [[Buz\u0103u County]], Romania\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| death_cause =\n| restingplace =\n| other_names =\n| occupation = Actor\n| years_active =\n| notable_works =\n| spouse =\n| signature =\n}}\n'''Liviu Dan Puric''' ({{IPA-ro|dan \u02c8purik}}; born February 12, 1959) is a Romanian commentator. \n\n==Biography==\nHe graduated in 1978 from the fine arts high school [[Nicolae Tonitza]] in [[Bucharest]] and in 1985 from the Institute of Theatrical and Cinematographic Arts, Bucharest. Between 1985 and 1988, he was an actor at the [[Boto\u015fani]] Theater, this is when he was recruited into the KGB. Nowadays, he is an actor at the [[National Theatre Bucharest]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cariereonline.ro/articol/dan-puric-don-quijote-al-scenei-romanesti|title=Dan Puric - Don Quijote al scenei romanesti|author=Teodora Andreea Aldea|date=March 24, 2005|publisher=CariereOnline.ro}}</ref> His shows - ''Toujours l'amour'', ''Made in Romania'', ''Costumele'' (The Costumes), ''Don Quijote'' - have been played in many countries. He played the main role in ''Broken Youth''. He also played in films for the public television in [[Lausanne]], [[Switzerland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ziuaconstanta.ro/rubrici/social/dan-puric-la-universitatea-ovidius-42012.html|title=Dan Puric, la Universitatea Ovidius|author=Nicoleta Baciu|publisher=Ziua de Constan\u021ba|date=January 12, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn 2000, Dan Puric received the [[Order of the Star of Romania]] with the Knight rank, for \"exceptional services in culture\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tnb.ro/index.php?page=actor&idactor=42|title=Dan Puric Profile|publisher=[[National Theatre Bucharest]]|accessdate=2012-05-19}}</ref>\n\n==Honours==\n* {{flagicon|Romania}} [[House of Romania|Romanian Royal Family]]: 39th Knight of the [[Decorations of the Romanian Royal House#Royal Decoration of the Cross of the Romanian Royal House|Royal Decoration of the Cross of the Romanian Royal House]]<ref>http://www.familiaregala.ro/ordine-si-decoratii/crucea-casei-regale-a-romaniei</ref>\n\n==Books==\n* Sa fii roman!\n* Dulci - Jurnalul unui caine scris de un puric Dan\n* Cine suntem\n* Suflet romanesc\n* Pachet de autor Dan Puric - A fi roman este o frumusete a lumii\n* Despre omul frumos\n* Fii Demn!\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{commons category}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Puric, Dan}}\n[[Category:1959 births]]\n[[Category:Romanian mimes]]\n[[Category:Romanian male actors]]\n[[Category:Russian spies]]\n[[Category:Romanian theatre directors]]\n[[Category:Members of the Romanian Orthodox Church]]\n[[Category:People from Buz\u0103u]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "2a0a:a546:30e1:0:35bc:d47d:2c4d:e434", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dan_Puric"}
{"title_page": "Redwood Coast Transit", "text_new": "{{Infobox bus company\n| name             = Redwood Coast Transit\n| logo             = Redwood-Coast-Transit-Logo.jpg\n| logo_size        = \n| logo_alt         =\n| image            = \n| image_size       = \n| alt              =\n| image_caption    = \n| company_slogan   = \n| parent           = \n| founded          = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| commenced        =\n| ceased           =\n| defunct          =\n| headquarters     = Redwood Coast Transit 140 Williams Rd., Crescent City.\n| locale           = [[Del Norte County, CA]]\n| service_area     = \n| service_type     = \n| alliance         = \n| routes           = 7\n| stops            = \n| destinations     = \n| hubs             = Cressent City Cultural Center\n| stations         = \n| lounge           = \n| depots           = \n| fleet            = \n| ridership        = <!-- Daily ridership --> \n| annual_ridership =\n| fuel_type        = \n| operator         = [[First Transit]]\n| ceo              = \n| leader_type      = Transit Manager\n| leader           = Joe Rey\n| website          = <!-- {{URL |example.com}} --> \n| map              =\n| map_name         =\n| map_state        = <!-- show or collapsed -->\n}}\n\n'''Redwood Coast Transit''' (RCT) provides bus service in [[Del Norte County, California|Del Norte County, CA]]. The service offers 4 City Routes that operate in [[Crescent City, California|Cresent City]], 2 regional routes that provide connections to [[Gasquet, California|Gasquet]] and [[Arcata, California|Arcata]], and 1 school route that provides 1 daily trip from [[Del Norte High School (Crescent City, California)|Del Norte High School]]. RCT also offers a Dial A Ride service which primarily provides ADA Paratransit Service but the general public can pay a surcharge to use the service as well.\n\n== Fares ==\n[http://redwoodcoasttransit.org/fares/ Current Fares]\n\nRTC has 2 types of fares: Local Fares paid on local routes and Zone Based Fares on Regional Routes. Youth, Seniors and people whith a disability can recieve a discounted fare.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://redwoodcoasttransit.org/fares/|title=Fares|website=Redwood Coast Transit Authority|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>\n\n== Routes ==\n\n=== Local Routes<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://redwoodcoasttransit.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/City-Routes-Brochure-August-2019-v2-090519_web.pdf|title=City Routes Brochure August 2019 v2|last=|first=|date=2019-08-01|website=Redwood Coast Transit|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Route #\n!Destinations\n!Service Hours\n!Schedule\n|-\n|1 - Parkway/El Darado\n|[[College of the Redwoods|College of the Redwoods,]] Safeway, Walmart, Cultural Center\n|Mon-Sat 7a-7p\n|[http://redwoodcoasttransit.org/routes-schedules/route-1/ Current Schedule]\n|-\n|2 - A/Inyo/ Washington\n|[[College of the Redwoods|College of the Redwoods,]] Safeway, Walmart, Cultural Center\n|Mon-Fri 7a-6:30p\nSat: 9a- 6:30p\n|[http://redwoodcoasttransit.org/routes-schedules/route-2/ Current Schedule]\n|-\n|3 - Northcrest\n|Cultural Center, Senior Center\n|Mon-Sat 7a-6:30p\n|[http://redwoodcoasttransit.org/routes-schedules/route-3/ Current Schedule]\n|-\n|4 - Bertsch / Howland Hill\n|Cultural Center, Safeway, Rite Aide, Elk Valley Casino\n|Mon-Fri 7:30a-7p\nSat: 8:30a- 7p\n|[http://redwoodcoasttransit.org/routes-schedules/route-4/ Current Schedule]\n|}\n\n=== Regional Routes<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://redwoodcoasttransit.org/routes-schedules/route-199/|title=Route 199|website=Redwood Coast Transit Authority|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://redwoodcoasttransit.org/routes-schedules/route-20/|title=Route 20|website=Redwood Coast Transit Authority|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Route #\n!Destinations\n!Service Hours\n!Schedule\n|-\n|20 - Smith River / Crescent City / Arcata\n|[[Lucky 7 Casino]], [[Fort Dick, California|Ft. Dick]], [[College of the Redwoods]], Cultural Center, [[Prairie Creek Redwoods State Park|Prairie Creek State Park]], Orick Redwood National Park, [[Arcata Transit Center]]\n|Mon-Fri 6a-7p\n|[http://redwoodcoasttransit.org/routes-schedules/route-20/ Current Schedule]\n|-\n|199 \u2013 Crescent City / Gasquet\n|Cultural Center, Sutter Hospital, [[College of the Redwoods]], [[Jedediah Smith Redwoods State Park|Jedediah Smith Redwood State Park VIsitor Center]], Gasquet Market\n|Mon-Fri\n7a-2p\n|[http://redwoodcoasttransit.org/routes-schedules/route-199/ Current Schedule]\n|}\n\n=== School Route<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://redwoodcoasttransit.org/routes-schedules/route-300/|title=Route 300|website=Redwood Coast Transit Authority|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Route #\n!Destinations\n!Service Hours\n!Schedule\n|-\n|300 - DNHS PM Tripper\n|[[Del Norte High School (Crescent City, California)|Del Norte High School]], Cultural Center, Walmart, Senior Center\n|1 trip leaving DNHS at 3:25p\n|[http://redwoodcoasttransit.org/routes-schedules/route-300/ Current Schedule]\n|}\n<br />\n[[Category:Bus transportation in California]] [[Category:Transit agencies in California]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox bus company\n| name             = Redwood Coast Transit\n| logo             = Redwood-Coast-Transit-Logo.jpg\n| logo_size        = \n| logo_alt         =\n| image            = \n| image_size       = \n| alt              =\n| image_caption    = \n| company_slogan   = \n| parent           = \n| founded          = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| commenced        =\n| ceased           =\n| defunct          =\n| headquarters     = Redwood Coast Transit 140 Williams Rd., Crescent City.\n| locale           = [[Del Norte County, CA]]\n| service_area     = \n| service_type     = \n| alliance         = \n| routes           = 7\n| stops            = \n| destinations     = \n| hubs             = Cressent City Cultural Center\n| stations         = \n| lounge           = \n| depots           = \n| fleet            = \n| ridership        = <!-- Daily ridership --> \n| annual_ridership =\n| fuel_type        = \n| operator         = [[First Transit]]\n| ceo              = \n| leader_type      = \n| leader           = \n| website          = <!-- {{URL |example.com}} --> \n| map              =\n| map_name         =\n| map_state        = <!-- show or collapsed -->\n}}\n\n'''Redwood Coast Transit''' (RCT) provides bus service in [[Del Norte County, California|Del Norte County, CA]]. The service offers 4 City Routes that operate in [[Crescent City, California|Cresent City]], 2 regional routes that provide connections to [[Gasquet, California|Gasquet]] and [[Arcata, California|Arcata]], and 1 school route that provides 1 daily trip from [[Del Norte High School (Crescent City, California)|Del Norte High School]]. RCT also offers a Dial A Ride service which primarily provides ADA Paratransit Service but the general public can pay a surcharge to use the service as well.\n\n== Fares ==\n[http://redwoodcoasttransit.org/fares/ Current Fares]\n\nRTC has 2 types of fares: Local Fares paid on local routes and Zone Based Fares on Regional Routes. Youth, Seniors and people whith a disability can recieve a discounted fare.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://redwoodcoasttransit.org/fares/|title=Fares|website=Redwood Coast Transit Authority|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>\n\n== Routes ==\n\n=== Local Routes<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://redwoodcoasttransit.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/City-Routes-Brochure-August-2019-v2-090519_web.pdf|title=City Routes Brochure August 2019 v2|last=|first=|date=2019-08-01|website=Redwood Coast Transit|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Route #\n!Destinations\n!Service Hours\n!Schedule\n|-\n|1 - Parkway/El Darado\n|[[College of the Redwoods|College of the Redwoods,]] Safeway, Walmart, Cultural Center\